cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method to enhance the social popularity of a post by recommending appropriate hash tags based on content and user popularity. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with social network services and user behavior. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is a possibility as the paper proposes an algorithm to incorporate user popularity and tag usage tendency into an existing algorithm. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possibility as the paper deals with images and videos uploaded to social network services. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implications of the proposed technology for individual users and companies/brands in social network services.
